### =============================================
### TASK API REQUESTS with Auto-Capture
### =============================================

### 1. Create Task (auto-captures taskId)
POST http://localhost:8080/tasks/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Read Linux book in the morning",
  "description": "Read chapters 5-8 of the Linux command line book",
  "priority": "HIGH",
  "status": "TODO",
  "userId": "{{userId}}"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("taskId", response.body.id);
%}

### 2. Create Second Task
POST http://localhost:8080/tasks/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Complete Spring Boot project",
  "description": "Finish implementing the task manager REST API",
  "priority": "MEDIUM",
  "status": "IN_PROGRESS",
  "userId": "{{userId}}"
}

### 3. Create Third Task
POST http://localhost:8080/tasks/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Write unit tests",
  "description": "Add tests for service and controller layers",
  "priority": "LOW",
  "status": "TODO",
  "userId": "{{userId}}"
}

### 4. Get Task By ID (uses captured taskId from request #1)
GET http://localhost:8080/tasks/{{taskId}}

### 5. Get All Tasks
GET http://localhost:8080/tasks/

### 6. Get All Active Tasks
GET http://localhost:8080/tasks/active

### 7. Get Tasks By Status
GET http://localhost:8080/tasks/status/TODO

### 8. Get Tasks By Priority
GET http://localhost:8080/tasks/priority/HIGH

### 9. Get Active Tasks By Status
GET http://localhost:8080/tasks/active/status/TODO

### 10. Get Active Tasks By Priority
GET http://localhost:8080/tasks/active/priority/HIGH

### 11. Get All Tasks By User ID
GET http://localhost:8080/tasks/user/{{userId}}

### 12. Get Active Tasks By User ID
GET http://localhost:8080/tasks/user/{{userId}}/active

### 13. Get Tasks By User ID and Status
GET http://localhost:8080/tasks/user/{{userId}}/status/TODO

### 14. Get Tasks By User ID and Priority
GET http://localhost:8080/tasks/user/{{userId}}/priority/HIGH

### 15. Check If Task Title Exists
GET http://localhost:8080/tasks/exists/title/Read Linux book in the morning

### 16. Update Task
PUT http://localhost:8080/tasks/{{taskId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Read Linux book in the evening",
  "description": "Read chapters 9-12 instead",
  "priority": "MEDIUM",
  "status": "IN_PROGRESS"
}

### 17. Update Task Status Only
PUT http://localhost:8080/tasks/{{taskId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "DONE"
}

### 18. Soft Delete Task (sets isActive = false)
DELETE http://localhost:8080/tasks/{{taskId}}

### 19. Hard Delete Task (removes from database)
DELETE http://localhost:8080/tasks/{{taskId}}/hard